"The user browses View 1 at the [Overview] level and learns about the relationship between soil type and crop yield across districts. Next, the user selects districts and soil types of interest by interaction through View 1, which updates View 2. In View 2, the user compares nutrient levels across districts at the [Exploration] level and selects specific districts for further analysis. This triggers View 3 at the [Detail] level, where the user analyzes nutrient ratios and their correlation with crop yield. Finally, in View 4 at the [Insight] level, the user uncovers variability and outliers in yield distributions across soil types and crops, refining insights dynamically through annotations and selections."